<br />
We all know, the smart phone integrates a large number of sensors to accomplish intelligent work. Different models of mobile phones, integrated sensors and the number of species also differ, but the most obvious motion sensors are generally inseparable.<br />
<br />
For example, used to measure the movement and posture of the accelerometer; used to measure the angular displacement between the three-axis gyroscope, it can measure the results of the accelerometer is corrected, the actual action of the user a more accurate judgments; in addition to be able to to determine the user's location magnetometer, GPS receivers or similar device.<br />
<br />
In addition to the sensor and sports-related, there are other types of phone sensors.<br />
<br />
distance sensor. The switch can be controlled by the distance of the screen during a call to identify the phone and face, and a microphone and an integrated camera sensor allows many users to capture perfect images.<br />
<br />
Environmental sensors. You can measure the temperature, pressure and light and a series of data, such sensors are generally arranged in the high-end models of smart phones can be used to measure the body temperature will be upgraded or dark environment screen brightness.<br />
<br />
Fingerprint sensor. Many phones now have fingerprint recognition feature, you can unlock or a host of other actions. For example, the Galaxy S7 and iPhone 6S are equipped with their own fingerprint sensor, Galaxy S7 can also be achieved through heart rate monitoring capabilities and built-in LED pulse sensor.<br />
